# ProtonVPN Configuration Reference

This directory stores ProtonVPN preference templates. The official ProtonVPN Linux
GUI and CLI manage most settings internally via the `proton-vpn-daemon`, so these
files serve as **declarative defaults** and a reference for your VPN setup.

## Templated Preferences (from chezmoi)

| Preference | Value | How to Change |
|-----------|-------|---------------|
| Protocol | {{ .vpn_protocol }} | GUI: Settings → Protocol, or CLI: `protonvpn c -p {{ .vpn_protocol }}` |
| Kill Switch | {{ .vpn_killswitch }} | GUI: Settings → Kill Switch toggle |
| Split Tunneling | {{ .vpn_split_tunneling }} | GUI: Settings → Split Tunneling (toggle on/off) |
| Custom DNS | {{ .vpn_dns }} | GUI: Settings → DNS (NetShield ad-blocker) |
| Auto-Connect | {{ .vpn_auto_connect }} | GUI: Settings → Auto-Connect |
| Secure Core | {{ .vpn_secure_core }} | GUI: Settings → Secure Core toggle |

## Per-Host Overrides

Edit `~/.config/chezmoi/chezmoi.toml` on any machine to override:

```toml
[vpn]
vpn_protocol = "openvpn"       # Switch to OpenVPN
vpn_split_tunneling = false    # Disable split tunneling
vpn_auto_connect = true        # Auto-connect on launch
```

Then run `chezmoi apply` to update this file.

## Split Tunneling

When enabled (default: {{ .vpn_split_tunneling }}), only apps added to the split
tunneling list route through VPN. All other traffic goes direct.

**To add/remove apps:** GUI → Settings → Split Tunneling → Add/Remove apps

This is useful for:
- Routing browsers through VPN while keeping gaming traffic direct
- Using ProtonVPN for specific work apps only

## CLI Quick Reference

```bash
# Connect to fastest server
protonvpn c

# Connect with specific protocol
protonvpn c -p {{ .vpn_protocol }}

# Connect to specific country
protonvpn c US

# Disconnect
protonvpn d

# Show connection status
protonvpn s

# List available servers
protonvpn cc

# Reconnect (same server)
protonvpn r
```

## Keyring Notes

ProtonVPN stores credentials in `gnome-keyring` (also works with KDE's KWallet).
First login is interactive: open the GUI app and sign in with your Proton account.
